{
    "_comment": "Copy this file to print_profiles_user.json (gitignored) and edit. Each grade is {radial, axial, slot}. 'radial' = half-extra on diameter (all features); 'axial' = along-axis allowance; 'slot' = additional half-width for narrow + cross slots (FDM tightens narrow slots more than the round envelope). 'slot' is OPTIONAL and overridable per grade — an omitted key loads as 0.0. The shipped print_profiles.json already carries a conservative slip.slot = 0.10 for fdm_standard, so most users only calibrate slip.radial. Override 'slot' here only on an unusual printer. User-defined profile keys are recommended to follow the <machine>__<material>[__<brand>] convention with __ (double underscore) as the separator — e.g. bambu_p1s__pla_overture. User overrides recursively deep-merge onto the shipped defaults (a single-leaf override inherits its siblings from shipped — see vibe_cading/print_settings.py module docstring). (This _comment key is not a real profile; the loader ignores it.)",
    "bambu_p1s__pla_overture": {
        "free":  {"radial": 0.15, "axial": 0.25},
        "slip":  {"radial": 0.05, "axial": 0.25, "slot": 0.10},
        "press": {"radial": 0.04, "axial": 0.25}
    },
    "saturn3_ultra__abs_like_resin": {
        "free":  {"radial": 0.05, "axial": 0.05},
        "slip":  {"radial": 0.03, "axial": 0.05},
        "press": {"radial": 0.02, "axial": 0.05}
    }
